               <p>WILLIAM BRADLEY. I am a <rs id="t18281204-250-viclabel1324" type="occupation">green-grocer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-250-victim2171 t18281204-250-viclabel1324"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281204-250-crimeloc1325">Old-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-250-crimeloc1325" type="placeName" value="Old-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-250-crimeloc1325" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-250-off1322 t18281204-250-crimeloc1325"></join>. Mullis has been employed by me occasionally; I saw him last Thursday afternoon near my premises with Rolf, and another person who has been acquitted - they were there three of four hours; I missed the canvas cloth from my back-premises, and suspected Mullis; I went to the officer, and took him to a house in Kingsland-road, kept by Myers - Mullis was with us, and 
               <persName id="t18281204-250-person2172">
                  Lewis 
                  Myers
               <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2172" type="surname" value="Myers"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2172" type="given" value="Lewis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             said in his presence that he bought it of two boys, but Mullis was not one; I had told Mullis if he would tell me where the property was, I would not punish him, and then he told us that he and the others had taken it, and it was at Myers'.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-250-person2173">
                  JOHN 
                  CLARKE
               <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2173" type="surname" value="CLARKE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2173" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2173" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a headborough of St. Luke's. I was present when Mullis was taken; as we were going to the watch-house Mr. Bradley questioned him; he said that he and two more had committed the robbery, and had sold the cloth to Mr. Myers, in Kingsland-road, and he stood outside while the other two went in.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-250-person2174">
                  JOHN 
                  KNIGHT
               <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2174" type="surname" value="KNIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2174" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2174" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took up Rolf, who said he knew nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-250-person2175">
                  LEWIS 
                  MYERS
               <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2175" type="surname" value="MYERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2175" type="given" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-250-person2175" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I bought the cloth on Thursday evening of Rolf, and another young man; I cannot say whether it was Mullis: I gave 2s. 8d. for it.</p>
               <p>ROLF'S Defence. I was coming down the road, and we met two men; one of them had the cloth on his shoulder: he gave us 6d. to take it in there.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoners received a good character, and were recommended to Mercy by the Prosecutor.</p>
               <p>ROLF - <rs id="t18281204-250-verdict1326" type="verdictDescription">
